name: Sportbike
description: Yamaha R15.The liquid cooled single overhead camshaft fuel injection engine churns out a maximum horse power of 13.5kW(18.4PS)/10000r/min and maximum torque of 14.2N.m (1.4kgf.m) / 7500r/min.

name: Cruiser
description: Triumph Bonneville Speedmaster 1200 motorcycle. In terms of performance, the bike gets a 1200cc, liquid-cooled, parallel-twin engine with a 270-degree firing order that makes 76.9bhp at 6,100rpm and 106Nm of peak torque at 4,000rpm.

name: Dual-sport
description: With electric start and a low seat height, the light, nimble and reliable XT250 is built to go wherever you go. On‑ or off‑road. Adaptable and comfortable with fat tires, a low seat and a smooth ride makes it a practical do‑it‑all, dual purpose machine

name: Dresser
description: The R 18 invokes our history and the iconic hallmarks of our brand which we have worked very hard on. A legacy that we live by every day in the spirit of #SoulFuel. The result: a cruiser full of character featuring a boxer engine with the highest cubic capacity we have ever built, plus timeless design features.

name: Sport-Tourer
description: There is a German proverb along the lines of “anyone who travels with ambitions never travels alone.” This is especially true when you are traveling with someone else. The BMW K 1800 GTL represents both these elements. It offers performance touring that leaves no wishes

name: Scooter.
description: If power and style are important to you then look no further. Zoopa Nova is the highest spec'd electric moped available in NZ. Our standard 72V 40Ah (2.88kwh) Lithium-ion battery is the most powerful battery of any electric moped currently available in NZ. That means more power for longer.

name: Standard.
description: Small in size but big on fun, the Kawasaki Z125 PRO motorcycle is a nimble streetfighter that makes a statement wherever it goes. With a 125cc engine, upright riding position and responsive street tires, it's your invitation to the rebellious side of fun.

name: Dirt Bike.
description: In motocross and all other off-road disciplines (KTM's main segment) manufacturers strongly adhere to one color to identify themselves. Red for Honda, blue for Yamaha, green for Kawasaki and yellow for Suzuki.
